Governor Chukwuma Charles Soludo of Anambra State has commiserated with Hon. Emeka Aforka over the death of his father-in-law, Elder John Eke-Eze. Governor Soludo recalled that the late Elder John Eke-Eze, who was a prominent community leader and peacemaker, dedicated his life to serving his community and humanity. The governor said the deceased’s selfless commitment and dedication remain a source of joy and inspiration to members of his community, both young and old. -Advertisement- According to the governor, it is comforting that Elder Eke-Eze lived a fulfilled and exemplary life worthy of emulation. Soludo admonished Hon. Emeka Aforka and his wife, Lady Lilian Aforka, to take solace in the fact that Elder Eke-Eze’s contributions to his community and his exemplary lifestyle as a devout Christian and dotting father will forever be cherished and remembered. The governor, on behalf of the government and the good people of Anambra State, prayed for the peaceful repose of the soul of the departed and that God grant the family the fortitude to bear the irreparable loss. Aforka who hails from Ndiowu represents Orumba North constituency in the Anambra State House of Assembly. He is also the Deputy Majority Leader in the House. POLL 